article.headline: Phoenix forge ahead with two second-half runs
article.linkText: Wisconsin-Green Bay topples Marquette for sixth straight win
article.story:
MILWAUKEE (AP) -- Kristy Loiselle scored 18 points, and No. 19 Wisconsin-Green Bay used two second-half runs to extend its winning streak to six  games with a 58-47 victory Wednesday night over Marquette.

Green Bay (12-2), trailing 28-26 early in the second half, sandwiched 9-0 and 8-0 runs around an 8-0 spurt by Marquette (8-4) to forge ahead 43-33 with 8:57 to play.

The Phoenix frustrated the Golden Eagles with tight defense throughout. Green Bay didn't allow Marquette to score consecutive baskets in the final 8:24 while extending its lead to 14 points with 2:04 remaining.

Rachel Klug scored 15 points for the Golden Eagles, who shot only 35 percent (19-of-55) from the field. The Phoenix shot 41 percent (20-49) but hit 52 percent (12-23) in the second half.

The Phoenix hit the game's first two shots, both 3-pointers,
then went scoreless for 7:31 and fell behind 9-6. An 8-0 run by
Green Bay was answered with seven straight by the Golden Eagles
before the first half ended with Marquette trailing 22-19.

   Both teams shot poorly in the first half, Green Bay making 31
percent (8-26) and Marquette 27 percent (7-26). The difference was
a 4-1 edge in 3-pointers.

Green Bay holds a 26-5 edge in the series, but Marquette had won
four of the last six games. The teams hadn't met since 1998.
	 
Elizabeth Dudley added 11 points for Green Bay.
